      • borderFlow

        public static void borderFlow(java.lang.String clusterHarden,
              java.lang.String qualityMeasure,
              double connThreshold,
              boolean testOne,
              boolean heuristic,
              boolean caching,
              java.lang.Integer minNodes,

              java.lang.String clusterOutput,
              java.lang.String output)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        The border flow clustering algorithm. for more information on the border flow clusterer @see Border Flow First step: processing the border flow clustering algorithm Second step: with the resulting cluster rank those clusters and for every feature tries to get a query by the best ranked cluster
        Parameters:
        clusterHarden - see Border Flow
        qualityMeasure - see Border Flow
        connThreshold - see Border Flow
        testOne - see Border Flow
        heuristic - see Border Flow
        caching - see Border Flow
        minNodes - the no of minimal Nodes a cluster should have
        inputQueries - the name of the file with the frequent queries
        input - the name of the file with the queries IDs and their similarity
        clusterOutput - the name of the output file in which the cluster should be written
        output - the name of the output file in which the resulting queries should be written
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Signals that an I/O exception has occurred.
